ng in Millington." data-buy="true" data-credit="Jabin Botsford/The Washington Post" data-title="\xc2\xa0Feb. 27, 2016" data-max-width="4419" data-image="https://img.washingtonpost.com/rw/2010-2019/WashingtonPost/2016/02/28/National-Politics/Images/Botsford_TRUMP_TN_16_02_27_11071456626011.jpg?env=A" data-ratio="1.5"> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-slide wp-volt-gal-photo" data-uuid="93c027b8-dcda-11e5-891a-4ed04f4213e8" data-caption="Christie introduced Trump after endorsing him before a rally at the Fort Worth Convention Center in Fort Worth." data-buy="false" data-credit="Tom Fox/AP" data-title="Feb. 26, 2016" data-max-width="3040" data-image="https://img.washingtonpost.com/rw/2010-2019/WashingtonPost/2016/02/26/Editorial-Opinion/Images/GOP_2016_Trump-0b841.jpg?env=A" data-ratio="1.332"> </div> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-title-overlay"> <div class="wp-volt-gal-title-backdrop"></div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-title-gradient"></div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-title-holder"> <div class="wp-volt-gal-title-main"></div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-title-subtitle"></div> </div> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-ad"> <div class="wp-volt-gal-ad-wrap"> <div id="slug_bigbox_gallery" style="display:none;"> <div id="wpni_adi_bigbox_gallery"></div> </div> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-ad-skip"> <div class="wp-volt-gal-ad-pie"></div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-ad-skiptext">Skip Ad</div> </div> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-close-fullscreen"><i class="close">&#215;</i></div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-main-nav wp-volt-gal-main-nav-prev"><i class="fa fa-angle-left"></i></div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-main-nav wp-volt-gal-main-nav-zoom"></div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-main-nav wp-volt-gal-main-nav-next"><i class="fa fa-angle-right"></i></div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-preroll"> <div class="wp-volt-gal-preroll-video"></div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-preroll-text"></div> </div> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-embed-promo-container"> <div class="wp-volt-gal-embed-promo-container-table"> <div class="wp-volt-gal-embed-promo-top"><span class="cell">Trump captures the nation\xe2\x80\x99s attention on the campaign trail</span></div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-embed-promo-mid"> <div class="cell"> <div class="wp-volt-gal-embed-promo-mid-img-container"> <img alt="" src="https://img.washingtonpost.com/rf/image_606w/2010-2019/WashingtonPost/2016/03/15/National-Politics/Images/BotsfordTRUMP160314OHIO37601458004038.jpg"/> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-embed-promo-mid-label"><i class="fa fa-camera"></i>View Photos</div> </div> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-embed-promo-bottom"><span class="cell">The Republican candidate continues to dominate the presidential contest.</span></div> </div> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-details"> <div class="wp-volt-gal-details-handle">Caption</div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-details-wrap"> <div class="wp-volt-gal-details-main"> <div class="wp-volt-gal-blurb">The Republican candidate continues to dominate the presidential contest.</div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-caption"> <span class="wp-volt-gal-caption-title">March 14, 2016\xc2\xa0</span> <span class="wp-volt-gal-caption-text">Donald Trump speaks during a campaign event at the Winner Aviation in Vienna, Ohio.</span> <span class="wp-volt-gal-caption-credit">Jabin Botsford/The Washington Post</span> </div> <a class="wp-volt-gal-buy-link" href="#" target="_blank">Buy Photo</a> </div> </div> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-templates"> <div class="wp-volt-gal-pie"> <div class="wp-volt-gal-pie-anim wp-volt-gal-pie-inner wp-volt-gal-pie-spinner"></div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-pie-anim wp-volt-gal-pie-inner wp-volt-gal-pie-filler"></div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-pie-anim wp-volt-gal-pie-mask"></div> </div> <div class="wp-volt-gal-interstitial-text">Wait 1 second to continue.</div> </div> </div> <style>.wp-volt-gal-preroll-video{width:100%;height:100%}</style> </div> </div> <script src="https://js.washingtonpost.com/video/resources/js/posttv/plugin.jquery.wp-preroll.min.js"></script> <script src="//js.washingtonpost.com/pb/gr/p/ssiSingle/rO609L1qgAmx7p/hi-pri-render.js?_=b56f8"></script> <script src="//js.washingtonpost.com/pb/gr/p/ssiSingle/rO609L1qgAmx7p/render.js?_=b56f8"></script> <script src="//js.washingtonpost.com/pb/gr/p/ssiSingle/rO609L1qgAmx7p/instance.js?_=b56f8"></script> </div> <div class="pb-sig-line has-headshot has-1-headshots hasnt-bio is-column"> <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/people/dana-milbank"><img src="https://img.washingtonpost.com/wp-apps/imrs.php?src=http://img.washingtonpost.com/news/opinions/wp-content/uploads/sites/10/2014/04/dana-milbank.jpg&amp;w=80&amp;h=80" data-threshold="480" class="pb-headshot pos-1 "/></a><div class="headshot-to-the-left"> <div class="bottomizer"> <span class="pb-byline" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">By <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/people/dana-milbank"><span itemprop="name">Dana Milbank</span></a></span> <span class="pb-role">Opinion writer</span> <span class="pb-timestamp" itemprop="datePublished" content="2016-03-14T03:05-500">March 14 at 3:05 PM</span> <span class="pb-tool email"><a href="mailto:dana.milbank@washpost.com?subject=Reader feedback for \'A day with Trump\xe2\x80\x99s true believers\'"><span class="fa fa-envelope"></span></a></span> <span class="tweet-authors"><span class="pb-twitter-follow unprocessed"><a href="https://twitter.com/@Milbank" class="twitter-follow-button" data-show-count="false" data-lang="en">Follow @Milbank</a></span> </span> </div></div><div class="clear"></div> </div> <article itemprop="articleBody"> <p> <span class="dateline">BOCA RATON, Fla. \xe2\x80\x94</span> It was a festive afternoon at the Sunset Cove Amphitheater. Families rolled out blankets on the lawn beside a man-made lake. Vendors sold foot-long hot dogs. Organizers tossed T-shirts from the stage. </p> <p>Then, at nightfall, Donald Trump took the stage \xe2\x80\x94 and things turned dark. </p><div class="inline-content inline-html left author-bio"> <div class="bio"> Dana Milbank writes about political theater in the nation\xe2\x80\x99s capital. He joined the Post as a political reporter in 2000. <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/people/dana-milbank"><b>View Archive</b></a> </div> <ul class="social-tools plain"> <li class="tool facebook"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/danamilbank"><span class="fa fa-facebook-square"></span>Facebook</a></li> <li class="tool google-plus"><a href="https://plus.google.com/117658160774941171422/"><span class="fa fa-google-plus"></span>Google+</a></li> <li class="tool rss"><a href="http://feeds.washingtonpost.com/rss/linksets/opinions/dana-milbank"><span class="fa fa-rss"></span>RSS</a></li> </ul> </div> <p>\xe2\x80\x9cOn Friday, we went to Chicago,\xe2\x80\x9d the billionaire presidential candidate told his supporters. They booed the mention of the Trump event that was canceled because of protests. \xe2\x80\x9cWe had some, I would say they were \xe2\x80\x94 let\xe2\x80\x99s be nice \xe2\x80\x94 \xe2\x80\x9d</p> <p>\xe2\x80\x9cA--holes!\xe2\x80\x9d a man near the front bellowed. The crowd laughed. </p> <p>\xe2\x80\x9cLet\xe2\x80\x99s call them protesters,\xe2\x80\x9d Trump suggested. The crowd booed.</p><div class="inline-content inline-video"> <div class="posttv-video-embed" data-aspect-ratio="0.5625" data-category-id="wirereuters" data-duration="54000" data-headline="Trump: \'There\'s no violence\' at campaign rallies" data-is-truth-teller="0" data-max-height="-1" data-max-width="-1" data-object-id="56e6eda7e4b02f10a5bb2216" data-show-endscreen="1" data-show-promo="http://s3.amazonaws.com/posttv-thumbnails-prod/thumbnails/56e6eda7e4b02f10a5bb2216/GOP_2016_Trump_Trade_691ff.jpg" data-uuid="f2b814dc-ea05-11e5-a9ce-681055c7a05f" data-youtube-id=""><script src="//js.washingtonpost.com/video/static/js/posttv/posttv-video-embed.v3.js"></script></div> <div class="inline-video-caption"> <span class="pb-caption">Speaking at a campaign rally in Hickory, N.C., March 14, Donald Trump criticized recent accusations that his rallies have taken on a violent tone. (Reuters)</span> </div> </div> <p>Trump mentioned one of his opponents, Florida\xe2\x80\x99s Marco Rubio. This produced a chorus of boos and insults: \xe2\x80\x9cHe sucks!\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x9cDeport him!\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x9cSend him back!\xe2\x80\x9d</p> <p>He mentioned another opponent, Ted Cruz. The crowd answered with a chant of \xe2\x80\x9cLyin\xe2\x80\x99 Ted!\xe2\x80\x9d and cries of \xe2\x80\x9cLiar!\xe2\x80\x9d and \xe2\x80\x9cHe\xe2\x80\x99s full of s---!\xe2\x80\x9d</p> <p>Trump mentioned Hillary Clinton. Audience members shouted: \xe2\x80\x9cF--- Hillary!\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x9cPut her in jail!\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x9cWaterboard Hillary!\xe2\x80\x9d</p> <p>He bemoaned the trade imbalance with China. One man rolled up his \xe2\x80\x9cSilent Majority Stands With Trump\xe2\x80\x9d sign and bellowed through it: \xe2\x80\x9cF--- China!\xe2\x80\x9d The crowd chanted: \xe2\x80\x9cBuild the wall! Build the wall!\xe2\x80\x9d</p> <p>To get a better sense of the Trump crowds, I watched Sunday night\xe2\x80\x99s rally here not from the penned-in press section but up front, in the crush of the crowd. I entered with the public and stood silently for four hours, near the woman whose cap said \xe2\x80\x9cInfidel\xe2\x80\x9d in English and Arabic, running my digital recorder. </p> <p>A couple of dozen people protested before and after the event, and a few people were removed during Trump\xe2\x80\x99s speech because of shoving. </p> <p>But it was relatively tame for a Trump rally, in part because Trump supporters fingered suspected infiltrators in the crowd and had them removed by private security guards before Trump spoke. In one of several such incidents I witnessed, Trump supporters signaled for security after a young man in a baseball cap who identified himself as \xe2\x80\x9cJohn\xe2\x80\x9d got into a political argument with some Trump fans. \xe2\x80\x9cGet him out!\xe2\x80\x9d one shouted. </p><div></div> <p>\xe2\x80\x9cI didn\xe2\x80\x99t say anything!\xe2\x80\x9d John pleaded as guards, taking the word of his accusers, led him away. </p> <p>An announcement before events advises participants not to harm those who \xe2\x80\x9chave taken advantage of Mr. Trump\xe2\x80\x99s hospitality.\xe2\x80\x9d But Trump has sent a different message, declaring Sunday that he might pay the legal fees of a man who sucker-punched a demonstrator and said his victim might need to be killed next time. </p> <p>The crowd Sunday evening apparently purged suspected \xe2\x80\x9cdisrupters\xe2\x80\x9d too thoroughly. \xe2\x80\x9cDo we have a protester anywhere?\xe2\x80\x9d Trump asked. Trump and his advisers seem to delight in the confrontations, which fuel the crowd\xe2\x80\x99s energy. Before Trump arrived, Trump aide Stephen Miller had just begun speaking when a woman near the front fainted. \xe2\x80\x9cMedic! Medic!\xe2\x80\x9d people shouted, waving signs and pointing. Miller, suspecting a protest, righteously condemned the \xe2\x80\x9ckind of person\xe2\x80\x9d who would \xe2\x80\x9csow chaos and disorder.\xe2\x80\x9d </p> <p>Those around me were almost all white and mostly men. Their T-shirts and caps said they were gun owners, veterans, Marines and Harley riders. I heard nothing racist or angry or paranoid in their conversations. But once Trump arrived, they became ominously transfixed and aggressive. They pumped their fists, flashed thumbs up, mouthed \xe2\x80\x9cThank you,\xe2\x80\x9d chanted \xe2\x80\x9cTrump! Trump! Trump!\xe2\x80\x9d and hung on the candidate\xe2\x80\x99s every word \xe2\x80\x94 often with looks of ecstasy and some visibly trembling.</p> <p>Trump captivated them with words that were alternately desperate and violent: \xe2\x80\x9cOur country is going to hell. .\xe2\x80\x89.\xe2\x80\x89. We\xe2\x80\x99re sitting on a very big, fat, ugly, bubble. .\xe2\x80\x89.\xe2\x80\x89. We\xe2\x80\x99re like the lap dog for the world. .\xe2\x80\x89.\xe2\x80\x89. Drugs are pouring across. .\xe2\x80\x89.\xe2\x80\x89. They\xe2\x80\x99re chopping off heads. .\xe2\x80\x89.\xe2\x80\x89. You see so many people being killed. .\xe2\x80\x89.\xe2\x80\x89. The jobs are being sucked out. .\xe2\x80\x89.\xe2\x80\x89. We\xe2\x80\x99re losing with everybody.\xe2\x80\x9d</p> <p>Before Trump spoke, a woman warmed up the crowd by reading tearfully from the autopsy report of her son, killed by an illegal immigrant (\xe2\x80\x9cslipknot around his neck\xe2\x80\x9d). \xe2\x80\x9cThe media is in an uproar about the tone of Mr. Trump\xe2\x80\x99s campaign,\xe2\x80\x9d she said, but not that \xe2\x80\x9cwe\xe2\x80\x99re burying our children every day at the hands of illegal aliens.\xe2\x80\x9d She accused Rubio of spending \xe2\x80\x9cblood money\xe2\x80\x9d and asked the senator which of his children he \xe2\x80\x9cwould give up for a foreigner to have a nicer life.\xe2\x80\x9d</p> <p>But happily for Trump\xe2\x80\x99s supporters, deliverance was at hand. The orchestral theme from the movie \xe2\x80\x9cAir Force One\xe2\x80\x9d played, and a helicopter flew low above the Trump fans, who raised signs and fists heavenward. </p> <p>Trump stepped out moments later to offer salvation. Twice he said that in a Trump presidency they could \xe2\x80\x9crelax\xe2\x80\x9d while he defeated the Islamic State and beat the world in trade. \xe2\x80\x9cWe\xe2\x80\x99re gonna become rich again,\xe2\x80\x9d he promised. \xe2\x80\x9cWe\xe2\x80\x99re gonna become great again.\xe2\x80\x9d </p> <p>From the passionate cheers sounding around me, I knew they believed him. </p> <p><strong> <i>Twitter: @Milbank</i> </strong></p> <p channel="wp.com"> <i>Read more from <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/dana-milbank/2011/02/24/ABhhJwI_page.html">Dana Milbank\xe2\x80\x99s archive</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/Milbank">follow him on Twitter</a> or <a href="http://www.facebook.com/danamilbank">subscribe to his updates on Facebook</a>.</i> </p> <div class="extra"> <p> <b>Read more:</b> </p> <p> <a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/post-partisan/wp/2016/03/13/donald-trumps-chicago-scam/" title="www.washingtonpost.com">Joe Scarborough: Trump\xe2\x80\x99s Chicago scam</a> </p> <p> <a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/plum-line/wp/2016/03/14/this-new-revelation-should-cripple-donald-trump-but-it-wont-heres-why/" title="www.washingtonpost.com">Greg Sargent: This new revelation should cripple Trump. But it won\xe2\x80\x99t.</a> </p> <p> <a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/stop-blaming-trump-supporters-for-campaign-violence/2016/03/14/33e45b7e-e9f1-11e5-b0fd-073d5930a7b7_story.html" title="www.washingtonpost.com">Marc Thiessen: Stop blaming Trump supporters for campaign violence</a> </p> <p> </p> </div></article> <div class="clear"></div> </div> </div> <div class="moat-trackable pb-f-theme-normal pb-1 pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-page-newsletter-inStream" moat-id="page/newsletter-inStream|opinions" data-chain-name="no-name" data-feature-name="no-name" data-feature-id="page/newsletter-inStream" id="f2oVlm1ACcB3Fp"> <div id="signup-box-instream" class="signup-box-instream "> <div class="hidden-data"> <p id="section-instream">opinions</p> <p id="subsection-instream"></p> <p id="blogname-instream"></p> </div> <div> <p class="headline headline-instream" id="headline-instream"><i class="fa fa-check checked-icon"></i></p> <p class="title tagline-instream" id="tagline-instream"></p> <p class="title confirmation-instream" id="confirmation-instream"> <span>Success!</span> Check your inbox for details. <span class="might-like"> You might also like:</span> </p> <div id="subscribe-form-inStream"> <input type="text" name="email" id="email-inStream" class="newsLetter-field" placeholder="E-mail address"/> <input type="submit" value="Add" class="newsLetter-btn subscribe-btn-inStream"/> </div> <input type="submit" value="Sign me up" class="newsLetter-field newsletter-btn-signed-up subscribe-newsLetter" id="loggedInBtn"/> <p class="error-msg-i